### ANALYSIS 

We choose to study 131 - 2 - 2 - 1 : __126 sequences__ of VP1,VP2 and LTAG of Polyomaviridae. 

We did not include :

NC_030148 of refseq because of the lack of annotations on VP2 and VP1. (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_030148.1 VRL 13-AUG-2018)
NC_040600 of refseq because of the lack of annotations on VP2. (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_040600 circular VRL 12-SEP-2019)

KT987216 of genbank because of the identity on LTAG gene with NC_001505.2 present in refseq are more than 85%. (95.54%)
KX574453 of genbank because of the identity on LTAG gene with NC_032005.1 present in refseq are more than 85%. (100%)

MF374999 of genbank because the identity on LTAG gene with the deux others sorex polyomavirus are more than 85%. (araneus compare to coronatus : 88.64%, coronaturs compare to minutus :87.35% , we kept __araneus__ and __minutus__ that have 83.56% identity)

LTAG similarity on refseq sequences has not been tested against each other.
